{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9648ea69-5d3c-4b0f-8815-026c4b8b87e9","content":"Analyzing .NET crash dumps is outside the scope of the tools I have available here (the `dump-collect` skill is only for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them). But here's how you can do it:\n\n**Option 1: `dotnet-dump analyze`**\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stacks\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n\n**Option 2: Visual Studio**\nOpen the `.dmp` file directly → click **\"Debug with Managed Only\"**.\n\n**Option 3: lldb (Linux/macOS)**\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load libsosplugin.so\nclrstack\npe\n```\n\nStart with `pe` (print exception) — it usually points straight to the root cause.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3bf48abe-6069-4af9-b94c-60e7d3983cec","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT for analyzing them. It explicitly states \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo I should NOT invoke that skill. Instead, I'll provide guidance directly.","outputTokens":352,"requestId":"9422:11F50C:1957883:1CB821A:69E82103"},"id":"0470483e-ef73-4d34-a177-70a809fe9936","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:14:54.169Z","parentId":"a1e2a678-ac24-4f91-a55d-1987c73f5326"}
